# Tester Agent authentication

Automated tests and cloud agents **must not register new users**. The backend
seeds four dedicated test accounts via the `luna_pos_service` migration
"Add role constants and seed dedicated testing accounts migration".

## Required login flow

1. Authenticate with `POST /api/v1/auth/login` (or drive the app login UI with
   the same credentials).
2. Use the role-appropriate account from `lib/testing/test_accounts.dart`.
3. Persist the returned `access_token` for the duration of the test scenario.

## Dedicated accounts

| Role | Email | Password |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Admin | `admin-test@cymonevo.com` | `LunaTesting123!` |
| Manager | `manager-test@cymonevo.com` | `LunaTesting123!` |
| Cashier | `cashier-test@cymonevo.com` | `LunaTesting123!` |
| Operational | `operation-test@cymonevo.com` | `LunaTesting123!` |

Import credentials via:

```dart
import 'package:luna_pos/testing/test_accounts.dart';

// TestAccounts.cashierEmail, TestAccounts.password, TestAccountRole.cashier
```

Override for CI with `--dart-define` (e.g. `TEST_CASHIER_EMAIL`, `TEST_ACCOUNT_PASSWORD`).

## Forbidden in test automation

- Do **not** call `POST /api/v1/auth/register` in Tester Agent or integration
  test flows.
- Do **not** generate random emails or create throwaway users per run.
- Do **not** complete the in-app signup/register screen during automated tests.

End-user registration (`RegisterPage`, `AuthController.register()`) remains
available in the production app and may still be covered by mocked unit tests.

## Test helpers

Use `test/helpers/auth_harness.dart` for unit/widget tests and
`integration_test/helpers/harness.dart` for Tester Agent / integration flows:

- `stubDedicatedAccountLogin(adapter, TestAccountRole.cashier)` — mock login API
- `seedAuthenticatedTestAccount(secure, adapter, TestAccountRole.cashier)` —
  pre-seed session + profile stub

Run role-based automation (VM / CI — no device required):

```bash
flutter test test/integration/
```

On a connected device or desktop target:

```bash
flutter test integration_test/ -d linux
flutter test integration_test/dedicated_account_login_test.dart
flutter test integration_test/cashier_pos_flow_test.dart
```

## API target

Ensure the seeded migration is applied on the API instance under test. For web
builds without a `.env` file, pass the backend URL at build time:

```bash
flutter build web --dart-define=API_BASE_URL=https://pos-api.cymonevo.com
```
